00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:11.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In Switzerland,
we are nobody, Pablo.

133
00:10:12.987 --> 00:10:16.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What good is having all the money
in the world if you can't go home?

134
00:10:24.206 --> 00:10:28.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we go back...
I'm going to have to fight.

135
00:10:36.594 --> 00:10:39.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do whatever is necessary,
my love.

136
00:10:51.025 --> 00:10:52.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Steve]<i> So, there it was.</i>

137
00:10:53.903 --> 00:10:56.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The decision that would</i>
<i>change Colombia forever.</i>

138
00:10:56.447 --> 00:11:01.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [excited shouting, whistling]
- [band plays up-tempo tune]

139
00:11:01.494 --> 00:11:03.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish]
You're way ahead in the polls.

140
00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:07.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In my opinion,
the outcome is decided.

141
00:11:07.958 --> 00:11:11.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My question is... why do you
keep getting involved with the narcos?

142
00:11:12.463 --> 00:11:14.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want a country at peace.

143
00:11:15.383 --> 00:11:17.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And if I don't do it, who will?

144
00:11:18.010 --> 00:11:19.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're backing them into a corner.

145
00:11:21.013 --> 00:11:22.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm wearing a vest.

146
00:11:23.933 --> 00:11:26.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid that a bulletproof vest...

147
00:11:26.143 --> 00:11:29.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
isn't enough to ensure
that you have a future.

148
00:11:31.816 --> 00:11:35.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, my friend.
There will be a future.

149
00:11:37.696 --> 00:11:40.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd chanting]

150
00:11:41.909 --> 00:11:44.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd applauding, cheering]

151
00:11:47.498 --> 00:11:52.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>Luis Carlos Galán</i>
<i>took the stage in Soacha on August 18th,</i>

152
00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:56.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>against the advice</i>
<i>of his campaign manager, César Gaviria.</i>

153
00:11:56.215 --> 00:11:57.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[overlapping chatter]

154
00:12:01.095 --> 00:12:03.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[automatic gunfire]

155
00:12:03.806 --> 00:12:08.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>The bullets entered just below</i>
<i>his vest and he was dead within minutes.</i>

156
00:12:08.102 --> 00:12:11.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>For a brief shining moment,</i>
<i>there was hope...</i>

157
00:12:12.064 --> 00:12:14.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>extinguished by the pull</i>
<i>of an assassin's trigger.</i>

158
00:12:16.694 --> 00:12:22.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>To mourn Galán's death, every hut in the</i>
<i>countryside lit a candle in remembrance...</i>

159
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:27.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and in the cities, thousands took</i>
<i>to the streets in a march of the silent,</i>

160
00:12:27.455 --> 00:12:30.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a mute protest</i>
<i>against the violence of the narcos.</i>

161
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:37.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>With Galán's murder... came the end</i>
<i>of hope for a peaceful future.</i>

162
00:12:37.965 --> 00:12:39.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Fabio sniffs]

163
00:12:41.802 --> 00:12:43.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish]
Let's speak clearly, brother.

164
00:12:46.932 --> 00:12:48.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Galán's dead.

165
00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:51.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You had him killed,
didn't you?

166
00:12:52.354 --> 00:12:54.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You didn't tell us shit,
and you killed him, you son of a bitch.

167
00:12:54.773 --> 00:12:57.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I want to go home, Fabio.
- Home?

168
00:12:57.651 --> 00:13:00.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why are we going home?
So they can capture us?

169
00:13:01.947 --> 00:13:06.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All this shit you talk about partnership,
and then you do this on your own? Huh?

170
00:13:12.416 --> 00:13:15.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Galán was the only threat.

171
00:13:15.920 --> 00:13:18.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is no one left to challenge us.

172
00:13:19.048 --> 00:13:20.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you know why, Fabio.

173
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:24.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because no one
has the balls that we have.

174
00:13:27.181 --> 00:13:29.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [sniffs]
- Going home.

175
00:13:33.395 --> 00:13:35.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>- </i>[Steve] <i>Pablo was right.</i>
<i>- </i>[sniffing]

176
00:13:35.272 --> 00:13:37.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Who would have the balls</i>
<i>to fill Galán's shoes?</i>

177
00:13:39.235 --> 00:13:40.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[bell tolling]

178
00:13:40.903 --> 00:13:43.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man speaking Spanish]
...that unique honesty.

179
00:13:43.656 --> 00:13:46.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As the people now rise
and call for justice,

180
00:13:46.825 --> 00:13:50.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I pray to God
that this sacrifice will serve at last...

181
00:13:52.122 --> 00:13:56.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as motivation for society
to react and bond...

182
00:13:56.752 --> 00:14:02.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to support the government...
and institutions...

183
00:14:02.174 --> 00:14:06.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
while also demanding
a more effective leadership,

184
00:14:06.929 --> 00:14:10.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
one undeterred by the hitmen,
the hijackings,

185
00:14:11.016 --> 00:14:14.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or any other manifestations of violence.

186
00:14:14.645 --> 00:14:17.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My father, Luis Carlos Galán,

187
00:14:17.815 --> 00:14:20.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
will be remembered
for awakening the Colombian people

188
00:14:20.150 --> 00:14:23.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to the danger of the narcos.

189
00:14:25.197 --> 00:14:29.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The assassin's bullets...
will not stop what my father began.

190
00:14:30.452 --> 00:14:34.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As he fell,
another rises in his place.

191
00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:38.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to tell Dr. César Gaviria...

192
00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:42.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the name of the people of Colombia,
and my family...

193
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:48.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that we entrust my father's ideals to him,
and that he can count on our support...

194
00:14:48.554 --> 00:14:52.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to become the president
Colombia wants and needs.

195
00:14:55.561 --> 00:14:59.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dr. César Gaviria, save Colombia!

196
00:14:59.189 --> 00:15:01.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[crowd cheering]

197
00:15:01.191 --> 00:15:04.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[crowd chanting]
Gaviria! Gaviria! Gaviria!

198
00:15:09.366 --> 00:15:10.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cheering]

199
00:15:10.784 --> 00:15:15.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>Dr. César Gaviria...</i>
<i>the new hope of Colombia.</i>

200
00:15:15.956 --> 00:15:19.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If he took Galán's position on</i>
<i>extradition, the narcos would declare war.</i>

201
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:23.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If he didn't,</i>
<i>the country would become a narco state.</i>

202
00:15:25.174 --> 00:15:27.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

203
00:15:32.723 --> 00:15:34.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[wife speaking Spanish]
Phone!

204
00:15:35.976 --> 00:15:38.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let it go to the answering machine.

205
00:15:42.066 --> 00:15:46.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- The machine's full.
- [machine clicks, beeps]

206
00:15:46.570 --> 00:15:48.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish it would stop ringing.

207
00:15:48.822 --> 00:15:52.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's your friends.
They're calling to offer support.

208
00:15:53.994 --> 00:15:57.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or opinions about what I should do.

209
00:15:59.375 --> 00:16:01.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why can't you run
without backing extradition?

210
00:16:06.799 --> 00:16:09.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I wrote those speeches.
- Yes...

211
00:16:11.178 --> 00:16:12.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but do you even believe in them?

212
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:18.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what I believe.

213
00:16:19.937 --> 00:16:22.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't want the narcos having free reign.

214
00:16:24.483 --> 00:16:27.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I don't want the United States
involved in our affairs.

215
00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:30.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So say nothing.

216
00:16:32.533 --> 00:16:34.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's the best way to stay alive.

217
00:16:38.580 --> 00:16:41.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[airplane soaring]

218
00:16:47.464 --> 00:16:49.967  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[up-tempo Latin music playing on radio]

219
00:16:51.218 --> 00:16:52.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Pablo] Gentlemen.

220
00:16:53.178 --> 00:16:56.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fernando, cheer up. Have a drink.

221
00:16:56.932 --> 00:16:58.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're going home!

222
00:17:03.564 --> 00:17:06.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- How are you? Hm?
- Fine, my love.

223
00:17:07.985 --> 00:17:09.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about you?

224
00:17:09.653 --> 00:17:10.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Give me one.

225
00:17:12.948 --> 00:17:14.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Margarita, right?

226
00:17:15.075 --> 00:17:16.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's see.

227
00:17:18.412 --> 00:17:20.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Son of a bitch, that's good.
- Right?

228
00:17:20.497 --> 00:17:24.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Thank you.
Listen, I've got a question for you.

229
00:17:24.376 --> 00:17:26.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[softly] Why are we going back?

230
00:17:27.504 --> 00:17:29.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're walking into a world of shit.

231
00:17:30.049 --> 00:17:33.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Relax, brother.

232
00:17:33.260 --> 00:17:37.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Spain's too far away
to protect our interests.

233
00:17:37.848 --> 00:17:41.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have a better chance
of influencing Pablo at home.

234
00:17:41.435 --> 00:17:46.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We need to be close by.
Relax. [chuckles]

235
00:17:46.815 --> 00:17:48.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you get it?

236
00:17:50.778 --> 00:17:54.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sniffs] He's only comfortable at war.

237
00:17:54.406 --> 00:17:56.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's taking us to the slaughter.

238
00:18:00.788 --> 00:18:04.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gacha chatters indistinctly in Spanish]

239
00:18:24.937 --> 00:18:26.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How's business?

240
00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:32.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Fucking Noriega is charging us a fortune,
but we got 175 tons to Miami.

241
00:18:32.820 --> 00:18:36.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Gacha's Mexican routes
are opening up Los Angeles.

242
00:18:37.908 --> 00:18:41.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But do you know what matters most
for our business, Pablo?

243
00:18:42.204 --> 00:18:45.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That the situation at home stays calm.
Know what I mean?

244
00:18:46.041 --> 00:18:47.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sure.

245
00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:04.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[softly] You should have
consulted with me about Galán.

246
00:19:06.061 --> 00:19:09.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You would have tried to talk me out of it.

247
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:10.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

248
00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:14.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I would have tried.

249
00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:19.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The amount of money we are losing
is because of that bullshit.

250
00:19:23.579 --> 00:19:24.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you listening?

251
00:19:26.123 --> 00:19:28.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look at those peaks, Gustavo.

252
00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:38.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll die...
before I ever leave Colombia again.

253
00:19:43.223 --> 00:19:45.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

254
00:19:45.684 --> 00:19:47.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[in Spanish]
What's happening, Carrillo?

255
00:19:47.352 --> 00:19:48.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[in English]
Thank you for coming.

256
00:19:48.729 --> 00:19:50.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I understand the narcos
are back from Panama.

257
00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:52.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[in Spanish]
So you practice your English with me?

258
00:19:52.357 --> 00:19:54.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[in English] Because these men
aren't cleared, and if we speak Spanish,

259
00:19:54.943 --> 00:19:56.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it could get back to Pablo.

260
00:19:58.197 --> 00:20:01.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So I started this to monitor
Pablo's <i>sicarios' </i>communications.

261
00:20:01.241 --> 00:20:03.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SAT phones, landlines, you name it.

262
00:20:03.911 --> 00:20:05.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got dozens of wiretaps,

263
00:20:05.329 --> 00:20:08.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I've only managed to seize
about ten kilos in the last month.

264
00:20:08.373 --> 00:20:11.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Probably because I've listened
to my own men tipping the narcos off.

265
00:20:11.585 --> 00:20:13.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So I've had to start surveilling them.

266
00:20:13.921 --> 00:20:16.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I listen to them
tell their girlfriends they're afraid...

267
00:20:16.632 --> 00:20:19.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
cry to their mothers
when one of our men gets shot down.

268
00:20:20.552 --> 00:20:23.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But every once in a while...
I hear them trade secrets with Pablo.

269
00:20:24.932 --> 00:20:27.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do your bosses know you're doing this?

270
00:20:27.809 --> 00:20:29.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I trust them even less.

271
00:20:30.187 --> 00:20:31.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Most of my men are from here,

272
00:20:32.022 --> 00:20:35.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where they can get to your mother,
your aunt, your cousin.

273
00:20:36.109 --> 00:20:40.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How do I fight... when my soldiers
are already working for Escobar?

274
00:20:42.366 --> 00:20:44.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, do they have to be from Medellín?

275
00:20:52.292 --> 00:20:53.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking Spanish] Yes.

276
00:20:53.794 --> 00:20:55.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I definitely like the red one best.

277
00:20:56.713 --> 00:20:59.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Really?
- Mm.

278
00:20:59.216 --> 00:21:00.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I prefer the gray.

279
00:21:01.593 --> 00:21:04.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Red is the color of the party,

280
00:21:04.471 --> 00:21:08.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and it makes you more...
sociable and close to the people.

281
00:21:08.350 --> 00:21:11.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- That's important.
- Mm.

282
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

283
00:21:13.313 --> 00:21:15.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wonder what Luis Carlos
would have chosen?

284
00:21:17.484 --> 00:21:20.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, we should
also hire an image consultant.

285
00:21:21.613 --> 00:21:27.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have to make you more appealing
to the youth, give you a more modern look.

286
00:21:27.661 --> 00:21:29.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now you are going to give me image advice?

287
00:21:29.663 --> 00:21:31.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm just thinking about the polls.

288
00:21:33.208 --> 00:21:34.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Anyway...

289
00:21:36.461 --> 00:21:41.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Galán had professionals at his side,
but which could he trust?

290
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:43.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hm?

291
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:46.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you know perfectly well
that you can trust me, right?

292
00:21:46.763 --> 00:21:48.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-hm.

293
00:21:50.142 --> 00:21:53.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, what are you going to choose,
red or gray?

294
00:21:56.523 --> 00:21:57.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

295
00:22:01.737 --> 00:22:04.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Luis Carlos said something to me
before he died.

296
00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:07.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"There will be a future."

297
00:22:11.455 --> 00:22:13.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now let's see what kind of future it is.

298
00:22:20.297 --> 00:22:22.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Duque]
We worked together in the ministry.

299
00:22:22.507 --> 00:22:24.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The idea that
he's a presidential candidate

300
00:22:24.926 --> 00:22:27.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
shows you our sad state of affairs.

301
00:22:28.638 --> 00:22:30.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need to know which side he is on.

302
00:22:32.017 --> 00:22:34.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He speaks with
the Foreign Press next week.

303
00:22:35.020 --> 00:22:36.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They'll certainly ask his position.

304
00:22:37.064 --> 00:22:39.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry, Pablo.
He'll be easy to influence.

305
00:22:39.858 --> 00:22:41.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- No, I disagree.
- Why?

306
00:22:41.485 --> 00:22:45.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I did an interview with him once,
when he was an economic advisor.

307
00:22:45.238 --> 00:22:48.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I found him sitting in the parking lot
in his beat-up Renault,

308
00:22:48.825 --> 00:22:54.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
eating a bag of apples...
and reading economic reform textbooks.

309
00:22:54.498 --> 00:22:57.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He was testifying to the cabinet
and wanted to be ready.

310
00:22:57.250 --> 00:23:00.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a bookworm, not a leader.

311
00:23:00.670 --> 00:23:02.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- No-- No--
- No, no, no, you're missing my point.

312
00:23:03.048 --> 00:23:05.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- No.
- He's not an oligarch.

313
00:23:06.218 --> 00:23:08.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's from modest circumstances.

314
00:23:08.178 --> 00:23:10.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Like you,
he's worked for everything he has.

315
00:23:11.264 --> 00:23:13.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have to be careful
with people like that.

316
00:23:22.818 --> 00:23:24.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[voice straining]
I want you to deliver a message.

317
00:23:26.363 --> 00:23:28.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jorge] We've made a lot of money.

318
00:23:28.532 --> 00:23:33.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What we have to decide is do we stick
with Pablo... or chart our own course?

319
00:23:35.080 --> 00:23:36.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[horses whinnying]

320
00:23:36.998 --> 00:23:39.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should talk to our friends down south.

321
00:23:39.459 --> 00:23:43.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, no. It's not time. No. Mm?

322
00:23:44.172 --> 00:23:46.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Whatever you say.
- [chuckles]

323
00:23:46.925 --> 00:23:48.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you seen Marina?

324
00:23:48.593 --> 00:23:50.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She told me she was
going to buy a new brush.

325
00:23:50.262 --> 00:23:53.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know your sister.

326
00:23:53.098 --> 00:23:57.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Her shopping expeditions take weeks.
- [both laughing]

327
00:23:57.602 --> 00:23:59.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[up-tempo Latin song plays]

328
00:24:03.817 --> 00:24:06.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have no idea how much
I wanted to go down on you in Panama.

329
00:24:06.236 --> 00:24:07.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

330
00:24:07.654 --> 00:24:11.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could tell that you really wanted to.

331
00:24:11.158 --> 00:24:13.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Come here, baby.
- You are very patient.

332
00:24:13.743 --> 00:24:15.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, of course.

333
00:24:15.996 --> 00:24:18.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All your people were there,
your brothers...

334
00:24:19.624 --> 00:24:21.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[moaning]

335
00:24:22.711 --> 00:24:24.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gustavo exhales]

336
00:24:25.672 --> 00:24:27.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighing]

337
00:24:27.465 --> 00:24:30.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My brothers are driving me crazy.

338
00:24:30.302 --> 00:24:31.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

339
00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:34.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You know what?
- What?

340
00:24:34.389 --> 00:24:36.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- They can go fuck themselves.
- [laughs]

341
00:24:36.975 --> 00:24:39.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they want to,
they can go live in Spain...

342
00:24:39.352 --> 00:24:42.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [both grunting]
- ...but you're staying here with me.

343
00:24:49.738 --> 00:24:51.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's not hide anymore.

344
00:24:52.032 --> 00:24:54.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Not anymore.
- [moaning]

345
00:24:55.493 --> 00:24:56.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

346
00:24:58.747 --> 00:25:01.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- What do we do about my wife?
- [both grunting]

347
00:25:04.711 --> 00:25:06.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ask Pablo to do us a favor.

348
00:25:07.839 --> 00:25:11.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just like he took care of Galán,
he can take care of your wife.

349
00:25:16.723 --> 00:25:17.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

350
00:25:19.476 --> 00:25:20.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You...

351
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:24.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are very evil for such a young girl.

352
00:25:24.606 --> 00:25:26.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

353
00:25:29.361 --> 00:25:31.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've moved up, Fernando.

354
00:25:33.531 --> 00:25:38.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From government minister
to Pablo Escobar's errand boy.

355
00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:43.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess the pay is much better.

356
00:25:43.875 --> 00:25:45.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not doing this for the money.

357
00:25:46.711 --> 00:25:51.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What country sends its own citizens
to an iron tomb in the United States?

358
00:25:52.300 --> 00:25:53.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand your dilemma.

359
00:25:54.052 --> 00:25:59.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Speak out in favor, you're seen as a US
puppet and you might not win the election.

360
00:26:00.976 --> 00:26:04.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Speak out against,
you anger the US...

361
00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:08.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and are criticized by our media
as a shill of the narcos.

362
00:26:08.566 --> 00:26:12.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
César, I was thinking I would love
to dedicate a program for your campaign.

363
00:26:12.237 --> 00:26:15.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would be an honor for me,
and would benefit us both.

364
00:26:18.034 --> 00:26:19.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What a great idea.

365
00:26:20.287 --> 00:26:22.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You guys are really shameless,
aren't you?

366
00:26:24.124 --> 00:26:27.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- How do you sleep at night?
- César, it doesn't have to be this way.

367
00:26:28.086 --> 00:26:31.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If Luis had been as smart as you,

368
00:26:31.923 --> 00:26:34.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
perhaps we could have avoided
this horrible tragedy.

369
00:26:36.636 --> 00:26:37.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We could have had peace.

370
00:26:38.138 --> 00:26:39.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Easy.

371
00:26:44.394 --> 00:26:45.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get out.

372
00:26:46.813 --> 00:26:48.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Read Pablo's letter.

373
00:26:49.733 --> 00:26:51.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe you will have a future.

374
00:26:54.237 --> 00:26:55.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

375
00:26:57.532 --> 00:26:58.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door closes]

376
00:27:02.537 --> 00:27:03.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knocking]

377
00:27:04.122 --> 00:27:07.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking English] They just picked up
that commie priest, Father Sobrino.

378
00:27:07.584 --> 00:27:11.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's gonna talk. And when he does,
I hope you DEA boys understand

379
00:27:11.546 --> 00:27:13.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
what's important in this hemisphere.

380
00:27:14.132 --> 00:27:16.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, how about you, uh...
clue us in?

381
00:27:16.801 --> 00:27:20.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Drug dealers, I mean, bad as they are,
they want your money.

382
00:27:21.097 --> 00:27:22.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Communists want everything.

383
00:27:23.058 --> 00:27:27.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know about you, Peña, but I...
I like to own shit.

384
00:27:28.146 --> 00:27:29.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right.

385
00:27:30.815 --> 00:27:32.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good talk, Lou.

386
00:27:32.150 --> 00:27:35.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Very, uh... enlightening.
- Yeah.

387
00:27:36.237 --> 00:27:37.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

388
00:27:39.449 --> 00:27:42.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This... priest?

389
00:27:43.161 --> 00:27:46.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If it comes out that he was your informant
and you protected him...

390
00:27:47.791 --> 00:27:49.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm gonna make sure
you're tried for treason.

391
00:27:55.799 --> 00:27:59.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>Peña had to figure out</i>
<i>how to get fake papers for Elisa.</i>

392
00:28:00.095 --> 00:28:02.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So he did what he does best.</i>

393
00:28:02.222 --> 00:28:05.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let me guess: it's a very
sad and complicated situation

394
00:28:05.266 --> 00:28:06.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
involving you and a beautiful local.

395
00:28:06.893 --> 00:28:10.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You got your nails done.
It's-- It's your color, Colleen.

396
00:28:11.898 --> 00:28:13.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- What do you want, Javier?
- It's simple.

397
00:28:13.525 --> 00:28:15.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just need your signature...
right there.

398
00:28:17.278 --> 00:28:19.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You want me to create an embassy ID?

399
00:28:19.572 --> 00:28:21.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Who is this woman?
- What I want you to do

400
00:28:21.533 --> 00:28:24.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is sidestep a little bullshit bureaucracy
and help someone stay alive.

401
00:28:25.912 --> 00:28:28.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You really think I'd be asking you
if it wasn't important?

402
00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:30.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's my informant.

403
00:28:30.583 --> 00:28:33.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And she could be the key to bringing down
the whole Medellín cartel,

404
00:28:33.086 --> 00:28:35.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so come on, Colleen,
whose side are you on?

405
00:28:51.688 --> 00:28:53.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish]
Cousin, what happened?

406
00:28:54.607 --> 00:28:55.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where were you?

407
00:28:57.068 --> 00:28:58.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- In the office.
- In the office?

408
00:28:58.778 --> 00:28:59.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

409
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:02.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is that where you were?

410
00:29:05.785 --> 00:29:07.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's weird...

411
00:29:08.246 --> 00:29:11.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because I called
and they said you hadn't been in all day.

412
00:29:11.791 --> 00:29:15.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know which office you called,
but I was there.

413
00:29:15.628 --> 00:29:18.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're seizing everything, Pablo.
All the accounts--

414
00:29:18.214 --> 00:29:20.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We knew there would
be a reaction with Galán, right?

415
00:29:20.967 --> 00:29:22.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

416
00:29:22.927 --> 00:29:24.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Relax, Gustavo.

417
00:29:26.264 --> 00:29:29.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Relax, because everything
will calm down later.

418
00:29:31.311 --> 00:29:33.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[fuse hissing]

419
00:29:39.027 --> 00:29:41.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are you gonna do?
Are you gonna kill us both?

420
00:29:41.946 --> 00:29:45.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- You afraid to die?
- No. Are you?

421
00:29:53.374 --> 00:29:55.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Put it out.
- Where were you?

422
00:29:56.044 --> 00:29:57.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Put it out, Pablo.

423
00:29:59.339 --> 00:30:00.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Put it out, Pablo!

424
00:30:09.682 --> 00:30:10.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you with me or what?

425
00:30:13.770 --> 00:30:15.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And when have I not been with you?

426
00:30:19.692 --> 00:30:22.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
From the beginning,
it has been you and me.

427
00:30:25.532 --> 00:30:28.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I cannot do this without you.

428
00:30:32.455 --> 00:30:34.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you doubting my loyalty, Pablo?

429
00:30:37.669 --> 00:30:39.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

430
00:30:42.090 --> 00:30:45.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I'm having serious doubts
about the Ochoas.

431
00:30:46.886 --> 00:30:48.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[slams dynamite onto table]

432
00:30:52.100 --> 00:30:53.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens]

433
00:30:56.020 --> 00:30:57.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [exhaling]
- [door closes]

434
00:31:09.492 --> 00:31:11.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Steve]<i> Gaviria read Pablo's letter.</i>

435
00:31:14.831 --> 00:31:16.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The terms were simple.</i>

436
00:31:17.166 --> 00:31:20.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>He promised peace</i>
<i>if the narcos were left alone...</i>

437
00:31:21.129 --> 00:31:24.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and if not...</i>
<i>he promised all-out war.</i>

438
00:31:25.049 --> 00:31:26.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

439
00:31:30.722 --> 00:31:35.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Carrillo with his wiretaps</i>
<i>knew a storm was on the horizon.</i>

440
00:31:36.311 --> 00:31:39.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Pablo became his duty</i>
<i>and his obsession.</i>

441
00:31:40.064 --> 00:31:42.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>He came to recognize Pablo's voice,</i>

442
00:31:42.609 --> 00:31:45.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>his sleep patterns,</i>
<i>what he liked to eat,</i>

443
00:31:45.612 --> 00:31:49.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>his tastes in art,</i>
<i>his love of silk sheets,</i>

444
00:31:49.198 --> 00:31:50.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and his favorite music.</i>

445
00:31:50.867 --> 00:31:54.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[up-tempo Latin music playing]

446
00:32:03.338 --> 00:32:05.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>He would die</i>
<i>for the love of his wife</i>

447
00:32:05.214 --> 00:32:06.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>when you'd hear him over the airwaves.</i>

448
00:32:11.054 --> 00:32:14.349  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But did she know</i>
<i>how easily he ordered his men to kill?</i>

449
00:32:14.432 --> 00:32:15.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking Spanish]

450
00:32:15.558 --> 00:32:18.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>He came to understand</i>
<i>that Pablo spoke in code.</i>

451
00:32:18.311 --> 00:32:19.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Pablo in Spanish]
Time to thin the herd.

452
00:32:19.771 --> 00:32:23.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>"Cattle" were judges</i>
<i>or politicians who supported extradition.</i>

453
00:32:23.274 --> 00:32:25.068  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But did we score a goal?

454
00:32:25.151 --> 00:32:27.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- The reporter, right.
- [boy protesting in Spanish]

455
00:32:29.405 --> 00:32:31.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's make sure
we score a goal on him as well.

456
00:32:31.783 --> 00:32:33.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve]
<i>A "goal" was a targeted assassination.</i>

457
00:32:34.869 --> 00:32:35.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, come on.

458
00:32:35.954 --> 00:32:38.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If you spoke out against him,</i>
<i>you were dead.</i>

459
00:32:38.539 --> 00:32:40.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>- The list grew by the week.</i>
<i>- </i>[Pablo] Ooh!

460
00:32:41.376 --> 00:32:44.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve]
<i>Guillermo Cano, editor of </i>El Espectador,

461
00:32:45.046 --> 00:32:47.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and his reporter, Luis Camacho.</i>

462
00:32:48.132 --> 00:32:52.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Jaime Rodríguez, the former head</i>
<i>of the anti-drug squad before Carrillo.</i>

463
00:32:52.971 --> 00:32:55.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The drumbeat went on and on.</i>

464
00:32:55.515 --> 00:32:58.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>For Carrillo,</i>
<i>the war had already started.</i>

465
00:32:58.309 --> 00:33:00.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But he just couldn't trust his army.</i>

466
00:33:00.311 --> 00:33:03.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish] You are aware
that I can end your military career?

467
00:33:03.856 --> 00:33:05.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I don't give a fuck.
- Excuse me?

468
00:33:05.692 --> 00:33:08.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Horacio... don't give up.

469
00:33:09.487 --> 00:33:13.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've always been the leader
of the persecution of Pablo Escobar.

470
00:33:13.241 --> 00:33:15.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is this how you show your appreciation
for all we've done?

471
00:33:15.451 --> 00:33:17.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This operation
could be a failure before it starts.

472
00:33:17.578 --> 00:33:19.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not here for fun.

473
00:33:19.956 --> 00:33:21.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's gonna happen
is the defense minister

474
00:33:21.666 --> 00:33:25.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
will give you credit for the evidence
that we found at Hacienda Nápoles.

475
00:33:25.169 --> 00:33:29.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So... then if you resign,
I will look really bad.

476
00:33:29.298 --> 00:33:31.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is that what you're doing?
Is that what you want?

477
00:33:31.509 --> 00:33:33.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Horacio...
you remember when we were cadets,

478
00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:38.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we never thought they would call us
to lead the country's most important unit.

479
00:33:39.267 --> 00:33:42.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Horacio, as your friend...
I'm asking you to think about it.

480
00:33:42.437 --> 00:33:44.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rodrigo, I don't even know who Pablo pays.

481
00:33:45.815 --> 00:33:47.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It could be any of us three.

482
00:33:48.109 --> 00:33:52.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Horacio, please.
- I've put my family at risk.

483
00:33:52.196 --> 00:33:55.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If there is going to be a war,
I need the right tools.

484
00:33:57.076 --> 00:33:58.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

485
00:33:58.786 --> 00:34:00.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perfect.

486
00:34:01.622 --> 00:34:03.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then tell me what you need.
Hm?

487
00:34:05.460 --> 00:34:07.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Incorruptible men.

488
00:34:07.795 --> 00:34:10.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve]
<i>And that's how the Search Bloc came to be.</i>

489
00:34:10.673 --> 00:34:11.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shouting]

490
00:34:22.685 --> 00:34:23.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[shouting in Spanish]

491
00:34:23.978 --> 00:34:26.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>But Carrillo</i>
<i>wasn't the only one recruiting soldiers.</i>

492
00:34:32.904 --> 00:34:35.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish] Hey, punk.
Are you all right?

493
00:34:35.907 --> 00:34:37.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Sure.
- Come here.

494
00:34:39.577 --> 00:34:42.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>La Quica and Poison</i>
<i>had kids deliver packages.</i>

495
00:34:42.914 --> 00:34:44.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And if they didn't look inside,</i>

496
00:34:44.665 --> 00:34:48.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>it meant they could be trusted</i>
<i>to deliver anything from cocaine to...</i>

497
00:34:49.670 --> 00:34:50.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>well, anything else.</i>

498
00:34:50.880 --> 00:34:53.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cheering]

499
00:34:53.174 --> 00:34:55.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chatter in Spanish]

500
00:34:59.639 --> 00:35:01.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[murmurs in Spanish]

501
00:35:06.312 --> 00:35:07.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Pablo] How are you, son?

502
00:35:09.524 --> 00:35:11.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- How are you?
- Good.

503
00:35:25.164 --> 00:35:28.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [thunder rumbling]
- [indistinct chatter in English on TV]

504
00:35:30.169 --> 00:35:32.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish]
I have to kill that son of a bitch.

505
00:35:34.257 --> 00:35:38.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Carrillo's a cop.
You can always buy a cop with money.

506
00:35:38.928 --> 00:35:42.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- I've tried, believe me.
- Then offer more.

507
00:35:42.974 --> 00:35:47.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Or I can loan you Navegante.
He will do whatever I ask.

508
00:35:51.482 --> 00:35:53.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[voice strains] That's true.

509
00:35:54.026 --> 00:35:59.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's silver or lead.
That's the choice for that bastard.

510
00:35:59.407 --> 00:36:04.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Speaking of lead,
I'm getting a shipment of weapons in.

511
00:36:04.495 --> 00:36:06.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uzis, grenades...

512
00:36:06.414 --> 00:36:12.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If I could find a nuclear weapon...
But now I'm negotiating a fucking missile.

513
00:36:12.420 --> 00:36:15.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- A missile? No fucking way.
- Yes.

514
00:36:15.590 --> 00:36:16.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Boss.
- Eh?

515
00:36:16.966 --> 00:36:20.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[President Bush] <i>This is crack cocaine,</i>
<i>seized a few days ago</i>

516
00:36:20.469 --> 00:36:22.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>by drug enforcement agents,</i>

517
00:36:22.722 --> 00:36:25.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>in a park just across the street</i>
<i>from the White House.</i>

518
00:36:26.142 --> 00:36:29.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>And our message</i>
<i>to the drug cartels is this:</i>

519
00:36:29.604 --> 00:36:31.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>the rules have changed.</i>

520
00:36:31.272 --> 00:36:33.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [Bush continues indistinctly]
- He's bullshitting, right?

521
00:36:33.649 --> 00:36:37.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's smoking that shit.
I guarantee it.

522
00:36:39.113 --> 00:36:40.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

523
00:36:40.448 --> 00:36:42.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gacha] Motherfucker.

524
00:36:44.827 --> 00:36:46.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm...

525
00:36:51.209 --> 00:36:55.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mrs. Quiroga told me
the neighbors on the block took a vote.

526
00:36:55.922 --> 00:36:57.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They want us to move.

527
00:36:57.423 --> 00:37:01.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we have guards stationed
outside the house 24 hours a day.

528
00:37:01.886 --> 00:37:03.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what scares them.

529
00:37:06.974 --> 00:37:08.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come here.

530
00:37:10.394 --> 00:37:12.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It won't always be like this,
my love.

531
00:37:13.022 --> 00:37:14.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knocking at door]

532
00:37:25.159 --> 00:37:26.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cocks gun]

533
00:37:37.797 --> 00:37:39.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Rodrigo.
- Hello, Horacio.

534
00:37:39.507 --> 00:37:41.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Everything OK?
- May I speak with you?

535
00:37:41.509 --> 00:37:43.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sure. Come in, come in.

536
00:37:44.887 --> 00:37:46.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Rodrigo]
<i>Let's talk about the incorruptibles.</i>

537
00:37:48.432 --> 00:37:49.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm listening.

538
00:37:55.982 --> 00:37:57.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

539
00:37:57.191 --> 00:38:01.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been instructed to tell you that
if you cease and desist your operations,

540
00:38:01.320 --> 00:38:04.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you will receive
a one-time payment of six million.

541
00:38:06.033 --> 00:38:08.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
