you left her at the altar.

566
00:39:50.262 --> 00:39:52.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know if she actually
made it to the altar.

567
00:39:52.223 --> 00:39:53.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

568
00:39:55.559 --> 00:39:58.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you saved her
a lifetime of hell.

569
00:39:58.479 --> 00:40:02.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, she forgave me. Eventually.

570
00:40:02.233 --> 00:40:05.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Married a stockbroker from Dallas.
- Hm.

571
00:40:05.820 --> 00:40:08.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Randy... I think.

572
00:40:12.159 --> 00:40:14.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Trust me, she's better off.

573
00:40:17.832 --> 00:40:20.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[sighs]
What if Father Sobrino talks?

574
00:40:22.711 --> 00:40:24.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's gonna talk.

575
00:40:26.757 --> 00:40:28.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Steve sighs]

576
00:40:54.201 --> 00:40:56.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Javier speaking Spanish]
It's about time, Navegante.

577
00:40:58.497 --> 00:40:59.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

578
00:41:00.082 --> 00:41:03.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking broken English]
Sorry I'm late. I couldn't came before.

579
00:41:04.670 --> 00:41:06.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Javier]
What do you got?

580
00:41:07.423 --> 00:41:09.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gacha's going tonight to Cartagena.

581
00:41:14.096 --> 00:41:15.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can help you get him.

582
00:41:15.931 --> 00:41:18.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You said you had information.
You didn't say Gacha.

583
00:41:20.227 --> 00:41:22.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess is your lucky day.

584
00:41:29.278 --> 00:41:31.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- What's the informant's motivation?
- Could be money.

585
00:41:31.947 --> 00:41:35.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The reward for Gacha is one million US.
I'd say that's pretty good motivation.

586
00:41:35.409 --> 00:41:38.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He spends his life on the run
if we don't catch him.

587
00:41:38.329 --> 00:41:41.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Something else going on with this guy.
- It's worth taking a risk.

588
00:41:44.418 --> 00:41:48.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Peña, you go to Cartagena.
Solely in an observational capacity.

589
00:41:48.756 --> 00:41:52.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We want this man captured alive,
if possible.

590
00:41:52.468 --> 00:41:53.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Murphy stays here in Bogotá.

591
00:41:54.011 --> 00:41:56.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gaviria's press conference is tonight,

592
00:41:56.347 --> 00:42:00.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I wanna be sure whatever
he plans to say, he gets to say it.

593
00:42:02.436 --> 00:42:03.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, ma'am.
[clearing throat]

594
00:42:04.021 --> 00:42:06.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's a beautiful dress,
Ambassador Noonan.

595
00:42:07.191 --> 00:42:08.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opening]

596
00:42:08.567 --> 00:42:11.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [Lou] Come on, Father. Ah, yeah. Talk!
- [Sobrino grunting]

597
00:42:11.654 --> 00:42:14.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[muffled groaning]

598
00:42:14.406 --> 00:42:17.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [Lou] Huh?
- [struggling grunts]

599
00:42:21.163 --> 00:42:23.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [sputtering]
- [Lou] Huh?

600
00:42:23.332 --> 00:42:26.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting] More? You want more?

601
00:42:26.460 --> 00:42:29.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No! No more, please! No more!

602
00:42:29.922 --> 00:42:32.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sobbing] No more!

603
00:42:32.258 --> 00:42:34.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ah, he's all yours.
He's ready to talk.

604
00:42:35.594 --> 00:42:36.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Father...

605
00:42:38.264 --> 00:42:41.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
how did Elisa Alvaro get away?

606
00:42:41.976 --> 00:42:43.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

607
00:42:43.727 --> 00:42:45.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaking Spanish]

608
00:42:50.109 --> 00:42:52.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [Sobrino sobbing]
- She left with the American woman.

609
00:42:54.697 --> 00:42:57.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [sighs]
- Murphy's wife.

610
00:42:58.701 --> 00:43:03.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just don't understand.
How'd you get involved with communists?

611
00:43:03.372 --> 00:43:05.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you actually met a communist?

612
00:43:05.457 --> 00:43:07.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, I have, actually...
and she lied to me.

613
00:43:07.918 --> 00:43:09.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I'm not a communist, Connie.

614
00:43:09.962 --> 00:43:13.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm fighting against poverty,
corruption, injustice and greed.

615
00:43:13.591 --> 00:43:16.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I guess Americans
don't have the same problem.

616
00:43:16.176 --> 00:43:17.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't we?

617
00:43:17.553 --> 00:43:19.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's not the same.

618
00:43:19.179 --> 00:43:21.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, I just wish
you'd been straight with me.

619
00:43:22.891 --> 00:43:24.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

620
00:43:24.852 --> 00:43:26.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perhaps I should go.

621
00:43:27.354 --> 00:43:31.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You can't just go.
Look, if they find you, they'll kill you.

622
00:43:33.027 --> 00:43:36.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I fell in love with a man...
with a good man.

623
00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:38.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I was hoping
to do something good.

624
00:43:38.949 --> 00:43:43.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But instead, I fell into something...
else, something more violent.

625
00:43:45.664 --> 00:43:47.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, that makes two of us.

626
00:43:50.294 --> 00:43:52.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Steve murmurs indistinctly]

627
00:43:53.881 --> 00:43:55.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll see you when I get home.

628
00:44:00.888 --> 00:44:02.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here, Elisa's ID.

629
00:44:03.015 --> 00:44:06.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- What am I supposed to do with that?
- Take her to Cumaral.

630
00:44:06.185 --> 00:44:07.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My contact there agreed to hide her.

631
00:44:07.770 --> 00:44:09.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs] While you go to Cartagena?

632
00:44:09.271 --> 00:44:11.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[mutters] I can't believe this shit.

633
00:44:11.482 --> 00:44:14.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Who made this?
- Brother, what do you suggest we do?

634
00:44:14.276 --> 00:44:15.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jump out of a window?

635
00:44:18.197 --> 00:44:19.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, she's...

636
00:44:21.492 --> 00:44:23.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- She's important.
- To who?

637
00:44:24.953 --> 00:44:26.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To us.

638
00:44:30.167 --> 00:44:31.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

639
00:44:33.754 --> 00:44:38.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I take care of Elisa...
you better fucking get Gacha.

640
00:44:44.765 --> 00:44:45.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[wife chuckles]

641
00:44:46.850 --> 00:44:48.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[speaking Spanish]
Finally, a romantic date.

642
00:44:49.853 --> 00:44:51.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's been a long time
since we've been alone.

643
00:44:51.563 --> 00:44:57.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mm. Just you, me...
and our bodyguard.

644
00:44:57.152 --> 00:44:59.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

645
00:44:59.988 --> 00:45:03.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Like the old days when we were young
and your father watched us.

646
00:45:03.784 --> 00:45:07.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Mm. My father adored you.
- [softly] Yeah, right.

647
00:45:07.371 --> 00:45:10.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [chuckles]
- [motorcycle idles outside]

648
00:45:15.295 --> 00:45:17.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [automatic gunfire]
- [patrons screaming]

649
00:45:20.300 --> 00:45:21.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

650
00:45:24.888 --> 00:45:26.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

651
00:45:27.141 --> 00:45:29.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- Garcia...
- [chaotic chatter in Spanish]

652
00:45:30.811 --> 00:45:32.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

653
00:45:34.064 --> 00:45:35.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

654
00:45:44.533 --> 00:45:46.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello? Yes.

655
00:45:51.248 --> 00:45:52.458  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

656
00:45:55.294 --> 00:45:56.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But he's all right?

657
00:45:59.840 --> 00:46:01.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

658
00:46:07.556 --> 00:46:09.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[exhaling]

659
00:46:13.103 --> 00:46:15.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[soft clattering]

660
00:46:17.733 --> 00:46:19.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ana?

661
00:46:19.610 --> 00:46:21.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[clattering continues]

662
00:46:30.621 --> 00:46:31.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ana?

663
00:46:40.964 --> 00:46:42.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ana?

664
00:46:46.386 --> 00:46:47.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ana!

665
00:46:50.724 --> 00:46:55.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- A little bird... came into the house.
- [chirping]

666
00:46:55.103 --> 00:46:56.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm helping it out.

667
00:47:07.991 --> 00:47:09.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

668
00:47:14.456 --> 00:47:16.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There was an assassination attempt...

669
00:47:18.585 --> 00:47:21.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on Colonel Carrillo.

670
00:47:21.129 --> 00:47:22.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did someone die?

671
00:47:23.632 --> 00:47:26.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs] One of his men.

672
00:47:28.136 --> 00:47:30.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
- [thunder rumbling]
- It must be terrible,

673
00:47:30.472 --> 00:47:32.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the position you're in.

674
00:47:32.808 --> 00:47:36.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to know
I think you are very brave.

675
00:47:38.897 --> 00:47:42.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not brave. Not like Galán.

676
00:47:43.860 --> 00:47:45.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That fear keeps you alive.

677
00:47:47.531 --> 00:47:50.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what none of them understand.

678
00:47:53.912 --> 00:47:57.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will support any decision you make.

679
00:48:04.881 --> 00:48:08.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Steve] <i>It's been said that</i>
<i>nothing gives the fearful more courage...</i>

680
00:48:09.553 --> 00:48:11.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>than another's fear.</i>

681
00:48:11.805 --> 00:48:14.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[audience murmuring]

682
00:48:14.975 --> 00:48:20.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Luis Carlos Galán</i>
